dismissalText.commentary: Saim Ayub b Fazalhaq Farooqi 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'im, stumps splattered! Scrambled seam and it runs on with the arm, inside Ayub's wild swipe, and the timbers take a tumble. Farooqi does what all fast bowlers love doing best, and Islamabad are off to the perfect start in their pursuit of second spot

dismissalText.long: c Hasan Ali b Shadab Khan
dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Haris c Hasan Ali b Shadab Khan 79 (39b 7x4 5x6 66m) SR: 202.56

dismissalComment.html: full toss, plinked to long-off! And Zalmi are behind the 8-ball now... Finally a misjudgment from Haris and Islamabad have the big wicket. Not the best ball Shadab's ever bowled, but somehow he coaxed Haris into checking his lofted drive, and it was catching practice for Hasan Ali coming in off the rope

dismissalText.commentary: Bhanuka Rajapaksa c Munro b Shadab Khan 41 (25b 4x4 2x6 51m) SR: 164

dismissalComment.html: slog-sweeps... but holes out! Munro is standing there waiting for the catch on the deep midwicket fence. He takes a couple of slow steps back, and eventually realises he's very close to the rope, so pops the ball up, steps out and back in, completes the catch. Smoothly done, and IU break the stand

dismissalText.long: c Sohaib Maqsood b Faheem Ashraf
dismissalText.commentary: Tom Kohler-Cadmore c Sohaib Maqsood b Faheem Ashraf 12 (5b 1x4 1x6 7m) SR: 240

dismissalComment.html: chipped to cover! Clean golf swing from Kohler-Cadmore but he slices it, and picks out the man inside the ring. Well snaffled by Maqsood above his head, another momentum-breaker for Isb

dismissalText.commentary: Haseebullah Khan b Mohammad Wasim 10 (11b 1x4 0x6 24m) SR: 90.9

dismissalComment.html: timbaaaaaaaaaaaaaaah! Pinpoiint yorker, a real sandshoe crusher and Haseebullah is cleaned up! Full and quick, 144 clicks and it thunders into the base of middle and off. See ya

dismissalText.long: c Fazalhaq Farooqi b Hasan Ali
dismissalText.commentary: James Neesham c Fazalhaq Farooqi b Hasan Ali 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: sliced straight to deep third! Hasan almost looks embarrassed by this, no celebration just a sheepish covering of the eyes. Full outside off and Neesham attempts to hit the cover of it - knowing that's what you have to do here - and sends it down the gullet of the man posted on the rope

dismissalText.commentary: Aamer Jamal b Hasan Ali 9 (11b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: bowled 'im! Length ball, maybe a little shape back in, Jamal swings across it and hears the crash of ash from behind. Top of middle and off stumps, job done. Again no celebration from Hasan

dismissalText.commentary: Khurram Shahzad not out 11 (15b 1x4 0x6 21m) SR: 73.33

dismissalText.long: c Shadab Khan b Hasan Ali
dismissalText.commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman c Shadab Khan b Hasan Ali 2 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: slower ball, miscued into the deep! Hasan has two in three and Zalmi are collapsing in a heap. Pace off and Mujeeb gets it wrong looking to heave over the leg side, picks out deep midwicket

dismissalText.long: c Salman Irshad b Khurram Shahzad
dismissalText.commentary: Hassan Nawaz c Salman Irshad b Khurram Shahzad 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: short and flapped... straight to short fine leg! Nawaz departs for a five-ball duck, and just like IU earlier in the day, Zalmi have the early wicket. The ball was dug in and cramped the right-hander, whose attempted pull ballooned up off the splice for a simple catch

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Kohler-Cadmore b Aamer Jamal 15 (16b 3x4 0x6 24m) SR: 93.75

dismissalComment.html: pitched up and drilled to mid-off! Jamal has another, he bellows in celebration. It was there to hit, but Hales couldn't get it high enough, picking out the man in the ring, Kohler-Cadmore, for a safe catch above his head. Zalmi really amongst 'em now

dismissalText.long: c Haseebullah Khan b Aamer Jamal
dismissalText.commentary: Sohaib Maqsood c Haseebullah Khan b Aamer Jamal 15 (6b 2x4 1x6 11m) SR: 250

dismissalComment.html: pitched up, and feathered behind! Strange shot from Maqsood, crouching low and looking to open the face on a dab behind square. It was a bit too quick for him, 141kph and kissed the toe of the bat through to Haseebullah. Zalmi have a second in the powerplay

dismissalText.commentary: Colin Munro c Aamer Jamal b Neesham 15 (14b 2x4 0x6 27m) SR: 107.14

dismissalComment.html: full, wide and slapped to deep point! Munro was hitting towards the shorter boundary, but maybe got it into the wind. Skewed off squarer than he was aiming and Jamal raced in to grab the catch. IU's hopes of a top-two spot are dwindling

dismissalText.commentary: Rahmanullah Gurbaz c Sufiyan Muqeem b Neesham 33 (24b 3x4 1x6 45m) SR: 137.5

dismissalComment.html: full, smoked... and grabbed low in the covers! Muqeem rises with his finger in the air, Neesham is grinning. Wide half-volley and Gurbaz went after it, maybe not the cleanest connection, and it's well held by the freshman tweaker diving to his right

dismissalText.long: c Saim Ayub b Sufiyan Muqeem
dismissalText.commentary: Shadab Khan c Saim Ayub b Sufiyan Muqeem 25 (19b 2x4 2x6 17m) SR: 131.57

dismissalComment.html: another googly, swatted to cover! It was dragged down and he could have put it anywhere, but mistimed his aerial cut and picked out the man inside the ring. Shadab shakes his head and stalks from the field, that might be second place down the gurgler

dismissalText.commentary: Asif Ali c Rajapaksa b Sufiyan Muqeem 5 (7b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: slogged straight up, Asif's gone! Muqeem strikes with the ball after his grab in the field. Another googly, spinning away from over the wicket, Asif looks to launch but only toe-ends it for a steepling catch at cover

dismissalText.commentary: Faheem Ashraf b Khurram Shahzad 38 (13b 2x4 4x6 18m) SR: 292.3

dismissalComment.html: yorked 'im! Shahzad finishes it! Surely. Superbly bowled, 139kph at the base of off stump. Ashraf has the big wind up but can only drop his bat in time to squeeze the ball into leg. Off fly the bails, and off fly the Zalmi players in pursuit of Shahzad

dismissalText.long: c Mujeeb Ur Rahman b Sufiyan Muqeem
dismissalText.commentary: Hasan Ali c Mujeeb Ur Rahman b Sufiyan Muqeem 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: tossed up and carted straight to deep midwicket! Went for the slog-sweep but didn't seem to fully go through the shot, easily held by Mujeeb jogging around the rope. United heading for the eliminator

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Wasim not out 14 (11b 3x4 0x6 13m) SR: 127.27
Fazalhaq Farooqi b Khurram Shahzad 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: yorked 'im, Part 2! Full and straight, beats a tentative prod and smashes off stump. Shahzad nails his brief and Zalmi have won by 13 runs, exorcising some of their Pindi demons in the process
